WEBVTT

00:03.770 --> 00:05.360
I just had the worst dream.

00:05.360 --> 00:06.980
-It was just a dream.
-No.

00:06.980 --> 00:08.310
This was a memory.

00:08.310 --> 00:09.410
The only way it's gonna stop

00:09.410 --> 00:12.030
Is if i can figure out who this masked guy is.

00:12.030 --> 00:13.950
I'm pretty sure it has something to do with my father.

00:13.950 --> 00:16.400
What is it that i need to know, dad?

00:16.400 --> 00:18.570
The truth about grandview, why you're here,

00:18.570 --> 00:20.240
The dangers you're facing.

00:21.710 --> 00:23.360
There's no record of his death?

00:23.360 --> 00:24.500
Not that i could find.

00:24.500 --> 00:26.340
No burial, no cremation.

00:29.300 --> 00:30.380
What are these numbers?

00:30.380 --> 00:31.730
I don't know. Must have pulled an old file folder.

00:31.730 --> 00:32.680
It's not my handwriting.

00:32.680 --> 00:34.820
Carl, i just saw you write them down.

00:36.830 --> 00:37.730
I mean, don't get me wrong.

00:37.730 --> 00:39.050
I respect the short order cook.

00:39.050 --> 00:40.280
They, after all, have built

00:40.280 --> 00:43.030
And maintained the temple that you see before you,

00:43.030 --> 00:45.220
But was that the best use of your father's law degree?

00:45.220 --> 00:47.570
I think he just took that job because he was on the run.

00:47.570 --> 00:49.040
Ooh, ok, now you have my attention.

00:49.040 --> 00:49.960
On the run from what?

00:49.960 --> 00:52.850
I don't know. But what's interesting isn't inside the file,

00:52.850 --> 00:54.100
it's what's on the front.

00:54.100 --> 00:55.730
At first i thought it was a phone number,

00:55.730 --> 00:56.700
But there's too many digits.

00:56.700 --> 00:57.650
And you're married,

00:57.650 --> 00:59.850
And any detective worth his weight in salt

00:59.850 --> 01:02.580
Can see that you have an enormous rock on your finger.

01:02.580 --> 01:03.860
You're not getting the point.

01:03.860 --> 01:05.450
The guy did not write this.

01:05.450 --> 01:07.440
A spirit using his body did.

01:07.440 --> 01:09.550
-You saw another possession?
-I think so.

01:09.550 --> 01:10.760
I searched the numbers on the web.

01:10.760 --> 01:13.590
I tracked 'em down as a social security number...

01:14.010 --> 01:16.160
What?What is that look?

01:20.760 --> 01:23.930
1979, is that a year or did you just graffiti my numbers?

01:23.930 --> 01:25.300
1979 is the year.

01:25.300 --> 01:26.890
It's a court case. It's a docket number.

01:26.890 --> 01:28.470
5 digits, followed by the year.

01:28.470 --> 01:30.430
Anybody knows that that has ever been sued

01:30.430 --> 01:32.720
Or sued or fought speeding tickets or several.

01:32.720 --> 01:34.630
-Haven't you ever done that?
-No.

01:34.630 --> 01:35.650
I fight all of mine,

01:35.650 --> 01:36.290
Even if i'm guilty.

01:36.290 --> 01:37.780
I feel like judges, at a certain time of day,

01:37.780 --> 01:39.130
They get tired, so they take pity-

01:39.130 --> 01:41.240
Ok, if it's a case, would it be online?

01:41.240 --> 01:43.190
I'm not sure, but you can check with the courts,

01:43.190 --> 01:44.820
'Cause once an arrest has been made,

01:44.820 --> 01:46.120
It's always public record.

01:46.120 --> 01:47.100
Thank you.

01:47.950 --> 01:49.070
What's the rush?

01:49.070 --> 01:51.560
Do you have any idea how long i have talked about

01:51.560 --> 01:53.080
Finding out what happened to my father?

01:53.080 --> 01:54.710
I mean, how he died,

01:54.710 --> 01:56.040
What happened to him before that?

01:56.040 --> 01:59.370
It's like... Somebody wants me to find out the truth.

01:59.370 --> 02:02.150
They were just waiting on me to ask.

02:07.090 --> 02:09.250
-Hey.
-Hey, stranger.

02:09.250 --> 02:10.720
Yeah, i know.

02:10.720 --> 02:11.910
Long night shift.

02:12.290 --> 02:13.480
Listen, i was on my way to see you,

02:13.480 --> 02:14.780
But then i started reading this,

02:14.780 --> 02:16.170
And i just couldn't put it down.

02:16.170 --> 02:17.790
Wait, so that number was a case file.

02:17.790 --> 02:19.170
Yeah, payne was right.

02:19.170 --> 02:21.960
It's a case that my father prosecuted when he was an a.d.a.

02:21.960 --> 02:24.140
It's so interesting, 'cause...

02:24.140 --> 02:26.240
You know, i was 9 when my dad left.

02:26.240 --> 02:28.500
And... My memories of him,

02:28.500 --> 02:30.480
Sometimes i feel like i made him up.

02:30.480 --> 02:31.750
But, reading this?

02:31.820 --> 02:35.100
What he had to say in court, it's like hearing his voice.

02:36.550 --> 02:38.220
<i>the state vs. Paul eastman?</i>

02:38.220 --> 02:40.200
Yeah, this little boy, michael wilkins,

02:40.200 --> 02:41.690
Was strangled in the woods.

02:41.690 --> 02:43.110
Paul eastman led them to his body.

02:43.110 --> 02:44.190
He was convicted of the crime,

02:44.190 --> 02:45.880
But that's all i really know.

02:46.310 --> 02:48.740
About the little boy, this case...

02:49.130 --> 02:50.610
Why i was led to it.

02:52.620 --> 02:54.150
It's just not enough.

02:55.810 --> 02:56.820
Hello.

02:56.820 --> 02:57.780
Can i help you?

02:57.780 --> 02:58.880
Hi, i hope so.

02:58.880 --> 03:00.860
Um, my name is melinda gordon.

03:00.860 --> 03:02.600
Are you ellen wilkins?

03:02.600 --> 03:03.340
Yes.

03:03.340 --> 03:04.720
Mom? Who is it?

03:04.720 --> 03:07.470
Oh, um, melinda, right?

03:07.470 --> 03:08.790
This is my son graham.

03:08.790 --> 03:10.710
Hi.I was looking for some information,

03:10.710 --> 03:13.180
And i think you might be able to help me.

03:13.180 --> 03:14.110
Ok...

03:14.110 --> 03:15.670
My father...

03:16.500 --> 03:19.110
Was the prosecutor for your son's case.

03:19.110 --> 03:20.870
His name is tom gordon.

03:22.230 --> 03:23.150
No.

03:23.150 --> 03:24.610
That was too long ago.

03:24.610 --> 03:27.020
Please. I know it's been years.

03:27.020 --> 03:29.110
My father's been missing almost as long,

03:29.110 --> 03:30.660
And i think that his disappearance

03:30.660 --> 03:33.840
Is tied to your son's death in some way.

03:34.760 --> 03:36.460
I really don't want to talk about it.

03:36.460 --> 03:38.590
And i'm so sorry to ask you to.

03:39.010 --> 03:40.700
We don't want you here.

03:46.090 --> 03:48.110
Uh, could i come in for a moment?

03:48.110 --> 03:50.570
You said your father's missing?

03:50.570 --> 03:52.860
The truth is, i think he's dead.

03:54.820 --> 03:55.820
Mom.

03:56.530 --> 03:58.010
Let's just see if we can help her.

04:00.700 --> 04:02.470
Well, i was researching the case,

04:02.470 --> 04:05.160
And the truth is, i don't have much to go on.

04:06.070 --> 04:08.230
Did you get to know my father at all during the trial?

04:08.230 --> 04:10.160
Don't talk about this! Make her leave!

04:10.160 --> 04:12.020
Why are you even listening to her?!

04:14.400 --> 04:15.330
Did...

04:15.330 --> 04:16.880
Did you see that?

04:16.880 --> 04:19.110
Oh, must have been the cat.

04:19.110 --> 04:22.220
Mom, you said you were keeping the cat out on the sun porch.

04:23.130 --> 04:24.520
Our daughter's allergic.

04:24.520 --> 04:26.620
My wife and i are here with the kids for a few weeks visiting

04:26.620 --> 04:27.920
while we work on the house.

04:27.920 --> 04:29.560
You should check on the cat.

04:29.620 --> 04:30.370
If she got out,

04:30.370 --> 04:33.100
She's probably in the pantry.

04:35.390 --> 04:37.950
-If there's a better time
-there's not.

04:37.950 --> 04:42.140
I don't know if you can understand this,

04:42.140 --> 04:44.340
But my youngest michael,

04:44.340 --> 04:46.250
This is still his home.

04:46.250 --> 04:50.200
And i can't, i won't, talk about his death.

04:50.200 --> 04:52.030
Not to you, not to anyone.

04:52.030 --> 04:53.810
Because i'm not dead!

04:55.600 --> 04:57.690
-Don't say that! Never say that!
-It's ok.

05:00.380 --> 05:01.740
Don't worry, honey.

05:02.380 --> 05:03.580
She's leaving.

05:05.610 --> 05:07.030
You should leave now.

05:07.960 --> 05:09.300
Stop, you're hurting me!

05:09.300 --> 05:10.210
How am i hurting you?

05:10.210 --> 05:11.470
Excuse me. Grandma!

05:11.820 --> 05:14.350
It's my turn! No, it isn't!

05:14.350 --> 05:17.090
-Tell her it's my turn!
-????

05:17.090 --> 05:19.540
Children, stop fighting!

05:19.540 --> 05:21.460
I told you we'd get in trouble.

05:25.170 --> 05:26.630
You kept his room.

05:28.140 --> 05:30.170
You made a place for him.

05:31.830 --> 05:34.220
Does everyone know he's here?

05:34.220 --> 05:36.560
Oh...Pierce, daisy,

05:36.560 --> 05:38.020
Go play in the guest room.

05:38.020 --> 05:40.390
Ok? It's all right. I'm not mad.

05:45.400 --> 05:48.480
Who are you, and what do you want, really?

05:49.750 --> 05:52.740
I can see spirits... Ghosts,

05:52.740 --> 05:56.010
And i can see your son, michael.

05:56.010 --> 05:58.370
You can see my son?

05:59.530 --> 06:00.810
Yes.

06:01.480 --> 06:03.840
Guessing that's not a shock to you.

06:06.610 --> 06:10.140
Michael loves his home and his family.

06:10.720 --> 06:13.460
He may live differently, but he lives.

06:13.460 --> 06:17.080
And that's not going to change, not ever.

